==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Syntony
<hw>Syn"to*ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Gr. <?/
agreement. See <er>Syn-</er>; <er>Tone</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld>
<def>State of being adjusted to a certain wave length; agreement or
tuning between the time period of an apparatus emitting electric
oscillations and that of a receiving apparatus, esp. in wireless
telegraphy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Syphering</ent>⟦br⟧
